##After recovering from drug addiction, he traveled to Africa to become a chief. This time, he donated, masks to the Drug Rehabilitation Center

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

The following article is from the Earth's youth map, the author of green

The alternative to being young

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 31, Zheng Yuefeng went to an international freight company in Lagos, Nigeria. He had a batch of face masks in his hand and wanted to send them to his country as soon as possible. The 14,000 surgical masks and N95 face masks are not easy to raise in Nigeria because they are imported, not produced locally, and because demand is low and stocks are tight everywhere.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Arriving at the freight company, Zheng found it harder to transport than to raise face masks. At the time, international flights to and from China were largely grounded. Not long ago, Zheng had just returned his ticket home for the Chinese New Year because his flights had been canceled. If the goods are stranded halfway, the freight company will bear some economic risk, many companies choose not to send orders to China. Zheng Yuefeng is the African Nigerian chief, the chief in the hearts of the local people have prestige, Zheng Yuefeng promised "the responsibility of a problem together" , freight company staff promised to try.

On Feb. 14, after two weeks of suspense, 14,000 masks arrived in Fujian Province, 10,000 of them in Fuzhou's judicial forced isolation drug rehabilitation center, and 4,000 in Jingyang, Fuqing city. The former is where Zheng Yuefeng struggled with drug addiction for 15 years, while the latter is Zheng Yuefeng's hometown.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zheng Yuefeng was received by the former president of Nigeria

When he first learned of the news of the outbreak of the Chinese epidemic, Zheng Yuefeng wept as he watched the news. Whenever the epidemic was mentioned, Zheng Yuefeng choked up, "Very Sad, very painful, I hope the motherland can be safe, the motherland's people can be healthy, I think I should do something. ".

This year is the fifth year that Zheng Yuefeng has successfully quit his drug addiction and come to Africa. During these five years, he founded a mining company in Nigeria, married a wife and had children, appointed vice-president of the Fujian Chamber of Commerce in Nigeria, vice-president of the Chinese Youth Association of Nigeria, and even as an African chief, "all the important things in life are done here" , but he is always thinking of his motherland.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Masks in packing

On January 27, the third day of the Lunar New Year, as in previous years, Zheng Yuefeng on wechat gave Wei Mingqing New Year greetings. Wei Mingqing, chief of the administration section of the judicial compulsory isolation drug rehabilitation center in Fuzhou, was Zheng's "benefactor and brother" who helped him get clean for 15 years between 2000 and 2015. After leaving the Drug Rehabilitation Center, Zheng Yuefeng has been in contact with him. Two people talk about the epidemic, Wei Mingqing said the Drug Treatment Center mask inventory is not much, hope Zheng Yuefeng help him buy 5000 masks in Nigeria sent back, Zheng Yuefeng immediately decided to add 5000, for the Drug Treatment Center 10,000 masks.

The next morning, Zheng Yuefeng set off.

The masks are not produced locally in Africa. They are all imported from India, China and Lebanon. The supply of masks is not large. All the masks in Lagos, where Zheng is located, have been sold out, zheng and his five other employees drove 300 kilometers from Lagos, and the six men split up, traveling from city to country, to drugstore after drugstore, buying 14,000 masks in three days. "I have been to countless pharmacies, one box is 50 masks, some pharmacies have one or two boxes, there are many pharmacies do not have at all, the most time is in a store to buy five boxes, this is a very large number. ".

Local mask prices are also rising. "One day at a time, all the masks in the country are sold out by the Chinese, " Zheng said. He bought the masks for 980000 naira, or more than one yuan each, it was a lot cheaper before.

It is also not easy to send masks from Africa to the country. Nigeria does not have direct flights to China. It has to make one or two connecting flights. Affected by the epidemic, many flights have been cancelled because of concerns about economic losses caused by goods being held up halfway, freight companies do not take orders at the beginning, Zheng Yuefeng repeated and freight company negotiations, and slowly wait for the freight company customs clearance, tax, check whether the mask is qualified. Zheng spent a total of 7,500 yuan, nearly half the mask price, that mask smooth arrival in the moment, Zheng said, "God bless! "

On February 14, three cartons of 10,000 face masks were delivered to a judicial compulsory isolation drug rehabilitation center in Fuzhou. The boxes read "Go China! Go Wuhan! Go Fujian! Go Fujian! " And were donated by Nigerian Chinese Zheng Yuefeng.

Chen Qiu, the director of the Drug Rehabilitation Center, was delighted. "When I was in charge of him, he was in his early 20s, with a clean face and a smart mind. " Although years had passed, Chen Qiu was still impressed with Zheng Yuefeng, and he remembered, he took Zheng Yuefeng on a lecture tour of the province.

Along with the mask was a handwritten letter from Zheng, saying, "I remember I was a Chinese. " "Zheng has not let you down. I have not touched drugs in the past few years. Without your guidance, I would not be the person I am today. "

In his letter, Zheng Yuefeng also wrote, "I don't have clothes, I'm in the same family with my son. " He saw a news report recently using this poem. The news was about overseas Chinese merchants in Henan snapping up supplies to help their hometown. Zheng Yuefeng was very moved, "The strong well-being of the motherland is very important for us overseas travelers. Once the motherland has something, we will make every effort to support it. Only when the motherland is well, can we these travelers live well abroad. ".

When the outbreak first started, Zheng donated 1 million naira (about 20,000 yuan) to the local chamber of Commerce. He heard that the first-line staff in Fuqing Jingyang town did not wear masks, and 4,000 masks sent to the home, also entrusted friends to the town of health care to send a value of 10,000 yuan. Later, a friend in Wenzhou found him and said that many units in Wenzhou, Zhejiang were in short supply of masks. He also helped to purchase more than 20,000 masks and sent them home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zheng Yuefeng and local staff

Five years ago, Zheng never thought he would have the chance to give back to his country and the people who helped him.

In July 2015, Zheng Yuefeng came out of Rehab for the third time. He had been looking for work for a long time, but he was hit with a wall everywhere, "Drug addicts return to society, the OSTRACISM is very severe, I was really very confused, and very afraid that they will use drugs again to numb their own. ".

This time, 40-year-old Zheng Yuefeng felt he could not bear the consequences of his relapse. He became an addict in 2000, when he was a teenager, and by 2015 he had been in and out of Fuzhou's Rehab three times, "I was the only child in my family, and my parents had great expectations of me. I broke their hearts and wasted the best years in Rehab. ".

He felt he could not find a job. In desperation, he thought of Chen Qiu, then the leader of the Third Brigade of the Fuzhou Drug Rehabilitation Center. Chen Qiu said, "there are no difficulties. All the police of the Third Brigade will always open their mobile phones for you. ". Zheng Yuefeng tried to call Wei Mingqing. Wei Mingqing understood the situation and offered his help enthusiastically. He suggested that Zheng Yuefeng try in a different environment and introduced him to a fellow countryman who was doing business in Africa, let Zheng Yuefeng have a chance to develop abroad.

Nigeria photographed by Zheng Yuefeng

In September 2015, Zheng boarded a plane to Nigeria alone.

When he first arrived in Nigeria, Zheng Yuefeng worked in a timber company introduced by his hometown and was responsible for purchasing pear trees and flowers in the mountains of rural Nigeria every day. Zheng Yuefeng did not feel any discomfort when he went to Africa alone. Although he did not know the language, he still thought Nigeria was a much better place than China, "because no one here is going to reject you or care that you're a drug addict. As long as you can work here, you can survive here. "

Zheng Yuefeng said he was "very honest" and "flexible" . After working in a timber company for three or four months, he made many friends. All his friends told him, "it's not cost-effective to eat death here. " The boss also suggested that he "Ah Feng, you go to buy a little wood, so you can earn a little more" .

Zheng Yuefeng barbecues with local people

"A Feng" listened to the suggestion of the boss, started his own timber business. He buys them from Nigeria, clears them through customs and sells them to China. Five or six of the original employees were friends he had met in Rehab, and when they heard he was doing well in Africa, they all came to him.

Timber Business let Zheng Yuefeng earned the "first bucket of gold" of life, 200,000 yuan. Every time I mentioned it, he would weep. Before going abroad, he borrowed 100,000 yuan for a month. He couldn't borrow any money. "I still remember the situation vividly. No one believed me. ". Zheng Yuefeng first time to make money things told Wei Ming Qing, he said Wei Ming Qing like his "re-parents" , without him, he would not come to Africa at all.

Zheng's timber business had been going on for two years, and the company already had more than a dozen employees, each earning more than 10,000 yuan a month. Later, because Nigeria will be listed as endangered pear flowers and trees, timber are banned, Zheng Yuefeng's business was stopped.

The mining area where Zheng Yuefeng company is located

Gold Mine in Delta

Instead, he set up a mining company. The company does the original gold business, picks out the sand gold from the channel mining, sifts, after burning sells directly in the local, the production line has two, the total investment reaches more than 30 million yuan. Zheng now works with local tyrants. He doesn't speak English well, so he uses Africans as translators. The business has gradually expanded from Chinese to African.

The successful experience of starting a business in Nigeria has given Zheng Yuefeng renewed confidence and won him recognition from Chinese businessmen in Nigeria. He is now vice president of the Fujian General Chamber of Commerce in Nigeria and vice president of the Nigerian Chinese Youth Association. Zheng Yuefeng feels that, "When you earn money, you give it back. ". He donated money to build a school for the region, which was built Youth Day, and the local chief and governor named him "chief" in recognition of his outstanding contributions.

The scene of Zheng Yuefeng conferring the title of Chief

Certificate of Chieftainship and crown

On the day of the investiture, the emperor of Yoruba people personally presented Zheng Yuefeng with a certificate and a sceptre symbolizing power. "I never thought I would become a chief in this land more than 10,000 kilometers away from China, " said Zheng, who danced to local percussion instruments and songs in a traditional white dress.

The chief was given a piece of land, and the people of the land became the chief's subjects, following the chief's name. When you go to see the governor, you get a direct audience. The local people also had great respect for the sheik, and when they saw him they knelt down and shouted "King, King" . Although the chief does not enjoy actual executive power, Zheng found that as long as he wore the chief's clothes, the local people would be very receptive to him and everything would be convenient and easy to do.

Zheng Yuefeng with his wife and children.

Many people feel that Zheng Yuefeng's life twists and turns, magic, Zheng Yuefeng also feel, "you let me how to imagine, I can not think to this stage. ". But now, what Zheng Yuefeng wants more is insipid, he plans to struggle again in Nigeria five years, return home to honor parents.

Over the past five years, the success of his career in a foreign country and the formation of a family have brought about a thaw in Zheng Yuefeng's relationship with his parents. Now that his daughter is with his parents in China, he video chats with them every day, "Now I feel like a human being, not letting my parents cry all the time. Now I hear and see my parents' genuine laughter every day, and I think that's the way life should be. "
